SIMPLE: stencil
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stencil
<hw>Sten"cil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably from OF.
<ets>estincelle</ets> spangle, spark, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧tincelle</ets>
spark, L. <ets>scintilla</ets>. See <er>Scintillate</er>, and cf.
<er>Tinsel</er>.]</ety> <def>A thin plate of metal, leather, or other
material, used in painting, marking, etc. The pattern is cut out of the
plate, which is then laid flat on the surface to be marked, and the
color brushed over it. Called also <altname>stencil
plate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stencil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stencil
<hw>Sten"cil</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Stenciled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Stencilled</conjf>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Stenciling</conjf> or
<conjf>Stencilling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To mark, paint, or color in
figures with stencils; to form or print by means of a stencil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stenciler</ent>⟦br⟧
